description: Data was loaded from the "ENSEMBL to All pathways mapping file" downloaded from the Reactome.org site on May 8th, 2016. More details: see http://www.reactome.org/download/current/Ensembl2Reactome_All_Levels.txt. For more information about the Reactome project, please see these recent publications: Fabregat et al. 2016 http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26656494; Milacic et al. 2012 http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24243840

fields.description: Ensembl gene or transcript identifier (eg ENSG00000136997 or ENST00000371953)
fields.name: gene_id

fields.description: Reactome pathway name. E.g., Transcriptional activation of p53 responsive genes
fields.name: pathway_name

fields.description: Evidence code (TAS stands for traceable author statement and implies manual curation, while IEA stands for inferred from electronic annotation)
fields.name: evidence_code

fields.description: Homo sapiens -- this table has been filtered from the larger Reactome database to include only human pathways and genes.
fields.name: species
